Job Description:
Data Scientist, Marketing (Imperva Inc., Plano, TX) – design, create, build, and maintain data warehouse that enables analytical and business intelligence-based marketing decisions. Duties include:

Aggregate and transform raw data from various data pipelines to improve processes, attribution and funnel optimization, pipeline reporting, and overall performance;
Map strategies to actionable and scalable tactics that effect change and influence outcomes;
Develop and maintain the data pipeline and dashboards that support our business development and marketing efforts and decisions;
Provide dependable marketing data to marketing leadership and stakeholder teams;
Aggregate, monitor, analyze and report on the health of the marketing organization, including recommendations on where to optimize marketing-sourced pipeline, engagement, lead quality, full funnel conversion rates, campaign KPI performance, and/or the effectiveness of spend;

Data Scientist Co-Op




Your Tasks and Responsibilities

Independently develop algorithms in R and/or Python to clean, process, analyze and visualize large multivariate datasets (genotypic, environmental, and phenotypic);
Work closely with data science team and business partners to break down complex business problems to build feasible solutions that are impactful, accurate and validated;

The Lead Data scientist will own and continue to expand the existing ML/AI frameworks we have built for automating the processing of invoices and the classification of restaurant purchasing data. This role will work closely with the leaders of Engineering and Data Science as part of the larger Data Science team reporting to our VP of Data Science. Our offering is a SaaS product delivered through a web interface and mobile application.&nbsp;
We serve owners and operators of independent restaurants to streamline their operations, save time and money, and allow them to focus on food and hospitality (and not paperwork). &nbsp;We process over 400k invoices a month and are on track to double that in the next year. &nbsp;Our goal is that a customer can take a picture of an invoice and see it reflected on their financial reports in minutes.&nbsp;
As a Lead Data Scientist, you will spend your day developing models, exploring new AI technologies, and exploring our data with the goal of minimizing the work needed to support our customers. We have years of R&D under our belt and proof that our models can have a meaningful impact on the restaurant industry.

